CNCP v1 23985
{
  "concept": "vuejs/core#5761: Duplicate key for transition group fragment when child has v-if",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:26:26.737569+00:00",
  "text": "Duplicate key for transition group fragment when child has v-if\n\n### Version\r\n3.2.33\r\n\r\n### Reproduction link\r\n[sfc.vuejs.org/](https://sfc.vuejs.org/#)\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\nHave a `<template v-for>` inside a `<TransitionGroup>`, with multiple children and one of those children has `v-if`. For example:\r\n```\r\n<template>\r\n  <TransitionGroup>\r\n    <template v-for=\"(item, idx) of ['A', 'B']\" :key=\"item\">\r\n      <div>{{ idx }}: {{ item }}1</div>\r\n      <div v-if=\"idx < 1\">{{ idx }}: {{ item }}2</div>\r\n    </template>\r\n  </TransitionGroup>\r\n</template>\r\n```\r\n\r\n\r\n### What is expected?\r\nHere the keys should be `A0`, `A1` and `B0`.\r\n\r\n### What is actually happening?\r\nBut instead we get `A0`, `A0` and `B0`.\r\n\r\n---\r\nWithout the `v-if` everything works correctly and we get `A0`, `A1`, `B0` and `B1`.\r\n\r\nIn the reproduction I have used a component for the children, so the generated key is easily visible in the devtools.\r\n\r\nRelated commit: https://github.com/vuejs/core/commit/4311dddfa72b405b20f469f8f219ec3027972f55\r\nRelated issues: #4718, #5360, #5392\r\n\r\n<!-- generated by vue-issues. DO NOT REMOVE -->",
  "language": "en",
  "keywords": [
    ":lady_beetle:  bug",
    "scope: transition",
    "has workaround",
    "🔩 p2-edge-case"
  ],
